26/04/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The head of the Turkish University Council (YOK), Erdogan Tezic, escaped an apparent assassination attempt Wednesday (April 25th), according to a statement from the top higher education board. 
It said that as Tezic, a prominent secularist, approached the YOK building, a man tried to forcibly reach him. 
Before running off, the man took out a gun and fired at security guards who intervened. 
No one was injured in the incident. 
(Vatan - 26/04/07; Reuters - 25/04/07)
